    <h2>Manufacturing Processes and Cross-Contamination</h2>

    <p>Cross-contamination occurs when gluten-free products come into contact with gluten-containing products or surfaces during manufacturing. This can happen in facilities that process both gluten-free and gluten-containing foods. To ensure a product is truly gluten-free, it’s essential to consider the manufacturing processes and whether the company has measures in place to prevent cross-contamination.</p>

